<dt class="">
Manager Financial Planning & Analysis EMEA (f/m) Sales & Markets 
</dt>
    <dd style="display: none;">
            <h4 class="headline-4">ABOUT THE JOB...</h4>
            <p class="text-grey">
As Manager FP & A EMEA (f/m) you will be the sparring partner of the Vice President Sales and Markets EMEA and supporting his team with reporting and analysis of the overall business. You will be responsible for the financial planning and analysis of Markets and Sales function in the EMEA region as well as coordinating the financial forecast process and all relevant FP & A activities. You will report directly into the Director Financial Planning & Analysis EMEA and will have the unique experience of working with all disciplines in the organization by providing reporting on key operational activities along with the long term strategic initiatives.

</p>
            <h4 class="headline-4">The responsibilities include:</h4>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
            
<li>Leading efficient and effective reporting, forecasting and accountability processes for different countries;</li>
<li>Coordinating the monthly forecasting process with the countries and the headquarter;</li>
<li>Working with sales operations and countries on pricing and ad hoc analysis;</li>
<li>Preparing of the annual business plan (key contributor);</li>
<li>Assisting in the development of financial models;</li>
<li>Providing ad hoc analysis and participating in special projects as needed.</li>

            </ul>
            <h4 class="headline-4">ABOUT YOU...</h4>
            <p class="text-grey">
You are a committed, reliable and detail-oriented team player with a flexible and supportive approach. Enjoying to work in an international environment along with a “can do” entrepreneurial mind-set is a must.
</p>
<h4 class="headline-4">YOU...</h4>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
               
 <li>Have a degree in a related subject and strong financial planning and analysis experience gained in an international environment;</li>
 <li>Have good working knowledge of US GAAP and internal controls;</li>
 <li>Have strong systems and analytical skills, particularly in MS Excel – BPC and Navision knowledge are a plus;</li>
 <li>Have the ability to work cross-functionally at all levels of the organization and to manage and prioritize multiple tasks on very tight deadlines;</li>
 <li>Have ideally gained experience with matrix organizations, high growth companies and branded consumer goods;</li>
 <li>Could already prove your business partnering skills and your ability to challenge;</li>
 <li>Are good in building convincing presentations;</li>
 <li>Have excellent Business English skills in speaking and writing;</li>
 <li>Love to barbecue and to promote the fantastic Weber lifestyle we create every day.</li>


            </ul>
<p class="text-grey">As a rapidly growing company, we offer you a pleasant international working atmosphere in a dynamic team, attractive compensation and benefits as well as many opportunities to take responsibility and to develop professionally.</p>
            <p class="text-grey"><b>Is this your dream position?</b></p>
