 <dt class=„">
Inbound Flow Planner for DK/NO/SW/UK (f/m)


</dt>
    <dd style="display: none;">
            <h4 class="headline-4">ABOUT THE JOB...</h4>
            <p class="text-grey">
As Inbound Flow Planner (f/m) you will be responsible for maximizing the product availability to customers while streamlining the inbound flow process and optimizing inventory levels. You will manage and coach the Flow Administrator and report directly to the Head of Demand Planning EMEA and work in conjunction with other departments.

</p>

            <h4 class="headline-4">The main responsibilities include:</h4>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
<li>Integrating and consolidating of the sales forecast at warehouse level;</li>
<li>Building a purchase plan and taking different criteria into account: recent sales forecasts, the Service Level Agreement, the EMEA inventory strategy etc.;</li>
<li>Keeping the purchase plan up to date in the ERP systems (Navision and SAP);</li>
<li>Participating in the sales & operations planning process by providing feedback to sales planners (e.g. shortages, inbound difficulties) and give feedback to the Distribution Department to plan the correct warehouse activity;</li>
<li>Controlling purchase orders on a daily basis (e.g. concerning time management, invoices);</li>
<li>Checking customs invoices and communicating inbound planning priorities to the inbound flow assistant to build an efficient inbound and production planning;</li>
<li>Building strong analysis on inventory in the warehouse, proposing action plans and building key reports on inventory;</li>
<li>Being responsible for the containers flow between the harbor and the warehouse.</li>
            </ul>
